rComments: Prof Rietti is really smart, you can see her struggling with stupid questions, she tries to be nice, but it is pretty obvious she finds it painful.
Rietti is a solid professor. Clear grading criteria and explanations. Fair assessments with respect to midterms, exams, quizzes etc Knows the material wells and knows how to convey it. A bit boring.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: 40% of your final grade is based on quizzes that you can do as many times as you'd like (I know right). Other than that there are 3 essays (20% each). Fair grader and will give you tons of help if you ask for it.

People are really too hard on this prof. She has a very dry sense of humour which I found hilarious, and she really does know her stuff. Not necessary to attend class but she covers the articles (which you have to write essays on) in depth so it is worth going to a few in order to write a good essay. All readings are online, so thats a bonus.

Professor Rietti is incredibly intelligent. She really knows her stuff. She has a dry sense of humour, and her quick- witted comments make the class and the material more interesting.   Take a class with her if you want to have a Prof that knows the course material (and beyond) in exceptional detail.

Boring. Barely heard her. She obviously wants this class to be online. 2 quizzes a week. Great topics to discuss but she didn't facilitate it. TA was a hard marker but it's not too hard to get marks. Just avoid her, not worth it. Only took it cause it's mandatory. Waste of time.
terrible
Lectures were very hard to follow. Lacked interest in material. Vague expectations for assignments. In-class exercises lacked merit and purpose. Had a great TA though.
Very interesting class, talked about very pertinent issues. Enjoyed it very much. Expectations were very clear. Clearly knew her stuff. Very useful online component. Recommended.
Though her interest in the material is evident, the classes were dull, her voice monotone and the essays unclear. Attended every class.. but not with excitement.

Easy class, attendance is now mandatory as you have in class assignments [you can hand them in later and she does post online but better to do in class] but honestly SO BORING. Almost comical as you talk about issues like abortion and euthanasia - but you will not get below a B I promise.

Felt bad for this prof - most students sleep or watch videos during her lectures. You really don't need to attend this class, everything is online. She is a really nice person, but not a captivating speaker. Follow her instructions when it comes to assignments and you will do well. Will definitely need her to clarify her expectations.

All material for course is provided online nor was it expanded upon in class. It is evident that Professor Rietti has a strong knowledge basis, however, she lacks communication skills and enthusiasm. Seemed uninterested at times. Group activities were redundant and impossible in such a large class. Her TA, Dave, was absolutely outstanding.
Depressing experience every lecture. Cannot communicate ideas effectively, should not be teaching. Just one more prof too stuck inside her own head.

Even though i really love ethics, i do not feel like this prof taught it well at all or explained any of the essential things that should have been. This prof was not helpful or approachable. I was disappointed because I really like ethics and the class was not stimulating at all. The format of the class was horrible. No one took her seriously.
bor, last name ing
Rietti is a very unhelpful person. She has such a negative personality. Barely any students attend her class because she's such an inept professor. Trust me, avoid her class.
She understands the material, but she is not skilled at communicating the material. She needs to become more enthusiastic in class.

A lot of people in this class are way too intense, you will do better if you just laugh your way through it. Prof Rietti is hilarious (very dry sense of humor) and the marking is extremely fair. There is no exam only 4 essays so if you write good essays this is the class for you.

She was extremely boring, speaks in a monotone robot voice.  She seems bored and half asleep. Not only that, but she is not a nice prof, she could atleast smile once. She has no sense of humour, she does not have a nice personality. Also marking is VERY unfair. TA's mark extremely hard on the essays, and give low marks. Never take a class with her.

Class was very boring, it's hard to pay attention when she gives off the impression of being bored, speaks in monotone, let class discussions get way off topic. I wouldn't take another class with her.
Should be a little more enthusastic when teaching, but I loved how she knew the material and made the mid terms and exams fair. One thing though, your T.A need to learn how to mark fairly though
Great prof. Really knows the material and is very clear. Very helpful in office hours, will patiently explain stuff til u get it. Will definitely take another class with her.

class could be good if it was smaller, the prof sounds like shes falling asleep or has taken too many pills and is falling into a coma= ur bored= u dont pay attention= u dont fail if u can write an essay :)

She only has 3 outfits... its fun to guess which one she's going to wear that day. The tests are fair, but you should probably read the text a bit. Ptinting the online notes make class easier.

Very bright individual and really tries her hardest to maintain the class' interest. The only issue is that she seems 'uncomfortable' speaking in front of large groups? Otherwise, a very interesting course with educational materal.
She is good at teaching the boring material.
Good Class. She is very helpful if you go to her office hours. She encourages a lot of discussion and really tries to get you involved. I would take another course with her in a second.

Workload was heavier than average but students were rewarded by being able to watch her lecture, move around, and write on the blackboard. Tuesday afternoons with Sophie were pure bliss. Excellent course
She lets people talk because she's interested in seeing how people engage with the subject - not good for the stupider people in class but for those of us who like the subject: great

Essay marking scheme is fair. In class she just goes through what the readings say. nothing novel or anything. You can skip 3/4ths of the classes and still get good test marks if you study. Discussions are excessive but good.

her class can get a little boring, because she lets the discussion go on and on....this wouldn't be a bad thing if the people in the class weren't so retarded.  For those of us who think and UNDERSTAND phi., then this course is pretty good!!
